According to the National Kitchen & Bath Association, the standard depth of a modern vanity, from front to back, is typically 21 inches. We base on countertop‚Äôs dimensions while measuring the depth, after all vanity‚Äôs depth is usually one inch smaller than countertop‚Äôs. This measurement is taken from the front of the top to the rear of the top. However, narrow depth bathroom vanities are available that measure less than 21 inches which are around 18 inches for smaller spaces. Using that standard number, anything with less depth than 21‚Äù would be something we consider a ‚Äúshallow depth bathroom vanity‚Äù. 

